data.value: Note to potential crackers: If you are trying to crack Bleu, dragging this exe into dnspy won't do much for you. This executable is written in C# and is a .NET application. Everyone with an ounce of knowledge about .NET should know that .NET apps can be decompiled. If you bypass any authentication here, you're not really doing much. The main authentication is in the DLL and can not be picked up by Fiddler. The server does not return anything static, so you'll have to figure out what the whitelist returns, modify something in memory, or modify the DLL itself to crack Bleu.
